Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.48,0:00:03.06,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,Dear Viewers Sitting in Front of the Television,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:03.06,0:00:05.23,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,the guys that appear in this anime are delinquents.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:05.23,0:00:07.94,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,So, please do not imitate what you see in this anime.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:07.57,0:00:09.98,Typeset,,0,0,0,,{\shad0\fnAveria Sans\b1\i0\bord0\blur0.3\fad(450,0)\c&HDADADA&\fs33\pos(362.532,49)}Do not imitate{\i1\fs40}!{\i0\fs33} Or this will happen{\i1\fs40}!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:18.83,0:00:23.79,OP Romaji,,0,0,0,,{\fade(250,350)\an8}僕が泣いているのは とても悔しいからです
Dialogue: 0,0:00:18.83,0:00:23.79,OP Romaji,,0,0,0,,{\fade(250,350)\an8}Boku ga naite iru no wa totemo kuyashii kara desu
Dialogue: 0,0:00:18.83,0:00:23.79,OP,,0,0,0,,{\fade(250,350)}The reason I am crying is\Nbecause I am very frustrated
Dialogue: 0,0:00:23.79,0:00:29.25,OP Romaji,,0,0,0,,{\fade(350,350)\an8}人の尊さやさしさ 踏みにじられそうで
Dialogue: 0,0:00:23.79,0:00:29.25,OP Romaji,,0,0,0,,{\fade(350,350)\an8}Hito no toutosa yasashisa fuminijiraresou de
Dialogue: 0,0:00:23.79,0:00:29.25,OP,,0,0,0,,{\fade(350,350)}I feel as though the nobility and\Nkindness of man is being trampled
Dialogue: 0,0:00:29.25,0:00:31.88,OP Romaji,,0,0,0,,{\fade(350,350)\an8}力を示す者達は
Dialogue: 0,0:00:29.25,0:00:31.88,OP Romaji,,0,0,0,,{\fade(350,350)\an8}Chikara o shimesu mono tachi
Dialogue: 0,0:00:31.88,0:00:34.51,OP Romaji,,0,0,0,,{\fade(350,350)\an8}しなやかさを失って
Dialogue: 0,0:00:31.88,0:00:34.51,OP Romaji,,0,0,0,,{\fade(350,350)\an8}Shinayakasa o ushinatte
Dialogue: 0,0:00:29.25,0:00:34.51,OP,,0,0,0,,{\fade(350,350)}Those who show their strength lose their grace
Dialogue: 0,0:00:34.51,0:00:40.06,OP Romaji,,0,0,0,,{\fade(350,350)\an8}ウソまみれドロまみれ じれったい風景でしょう
Dialogue: 0,0:00:34.51,0:00:40.06,OP Romaji,,0,0,0,,{\fade(350,350)\an8}Uso-mamire doro-mamire jirettai fuukei desho
Dialogue: 0,0:00:34.51,0:00:40.06,OP,,0,0,0,,{\fade(350,350)}Covered in dirt and lies, isn't it a vexing sight?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:40.06,0:00:45.35,OP Romaji,,0,0,0,,{\fade(350,350)\an8}より強くしたたかに タフな生き方をしましょう
Dialogue: 0,0:00:40.06,0:00:45.35,OP Romaji,,0,0,0,,{\fade(350,350)\an8}Yori tsuyoku shitataka ni tafu na ikikata o shimashou
Dialogue: 0,0:00:40.06,0:00:45.35,OP,,0,0,0,,{\fade(350,350)}Let's live more strongly, fiercely, and tougher
Dialogue: 0,0:00:45.35,0:00:47.61,OP Romaji,,0,0,0,,{\fade(350,350)\an8}まっすぐ歩きましょう
Dialogue: 0,0:00:45.35,0:00:47.61,OP Romaji,,0,0,0,,{\fade(350,350)\an8}Massugu arukimasho
Dialogue: 0,0:00:45.35,0:00:47.61,OP,,0,0,0,,{\fade(350,350)}Let's walk straight
Dialogue: 0,0:00:47.61,0:00:51.94,OP Romaji,,0,0,0,,{\fade(350,350)\an8}風は向かい風
Dialogue: 0,0:00:47.61,0:00:51.94,OP Romaji,,0,0,0,,{\fade(350,350)\an8}Kaze wa mukai kaze
Dialogue: 0,0:00:47.61,0:00:51.94,OP,,0,0,0,,{\fade(350,350)}The wind is against us
Dialogue: 0,0:00:53.44,0:00:58.78,OP Romaji,,0,0,0,,{\fade(350,350)\an8}どけ どけ どけ 後ろめたい奴はどけ
Dialogue: 0,0:00:53.44,0:00:58.78,OP Romaji,,0,0,0,,{\fade(350,350)\an8}Doke doke doke ushirometai yatsu wa doke
Dialogue: 0,0:00:53.44,0:00:58.78,OP,,0,0,0,,{\fade(350,350)}Move, move, move, those with\Na guilty conscience, move aside
Dialogue: 0,0:00:58.78,0:01:03.41,OP Romaji,,0,0,0,,{\fade(350,350)\an8}有象無象の町に 灯りをともせ
Dialogue: 0,0:00:58.78,0:01:03.41,OP Romaji,,0,0,0,,{\fade(350,350)\an8}Uzoumuzou no machi ni akari o tomose
Dialogue: 0,0:00:58.78,0:01:03.41,OP,,0,0,0,,{\fade(350,350)}Light up the town of riffraff
Dialogue: 0,0:01:04.00,0:01:08.88,OP Romaji,,0,0,0,,{\fade(350,350)\an8}どけ そこ どけ 真実のお通りだ
Dialogue: 0,0:01:04.00,0:01:08.88,OP Romaji,,0,0,0,,{\fade(350,350)\an8}Doke soko doke shinjitsu no otouri da
Dialogue: 0,0:01:04.00,0:01:08.88,OP,,0,0,0,,{\fade(350,350)}Move, make way, truth is coming through
Dialogue: 0,0:01:09.34,0:01:11.84,OP Romaji,,0,0,0,,{\fade(350,350)\an8}正義の時代がくるさ
Dialogue: 0,0:01:09.34,0:01:11.84,OP Romaji,,0,0,0,,{\fade(350,350)\an8}Seigi no jidai ga kuru sa
Dialogue: 0,0:01:09.34,0:01:11.84,OP,,0,0,0,,{\fade(350,350)}The era of justice will come
Dialogue: 0,0:01:11.84,0:01:14.55,OP Romaji,,0,0,0,,{\fade(350,350)\an8}希望の歌もあるさ
Dialogue: 0,0:01:11.84,0:01:14.55,OP Romaji,,0,0,0,,{\fade(350,350)\an8}Kibou no uta mo aru sa
Dialogue: 0,0:01:11.84,0:01:14.51,OP,,0,0,0,,{\fade(350,350)}There are songs of hope too
Dialogue: 0,0:01:14.55,0:01:20.35,OP Romaji,,0,0,0,,{\fad(350,500)\an8}僕の命この世に 捧げてしまっていいさ
Dialogue: 0,0:01:14.55,0:01:20.35,OP Romaji,,0,0,0,,{\fad(350,500)\an8}Boku no inochi kono yo ni sasagete-shimatte ii sa
Dialogue: 0,0:01:14.55,0:01:20.35,OP,,0,0,0,,{\fad(350,500)}I would happily sacrifice my life for this world
Dialogue: 0,0:01:31.07,0:01:32.69,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,I wanna go to Koshien.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:32.94,0:01:34.74,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,That's impossible with your attention span.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:34.74,0:01:38.70,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,I see... I wonder if it's really\Nimpossible for me to go to Koshien?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:40.24,0:01:41.91,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,You'll be fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:41.91,0:01:44.41,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,All you need is the passion\Nto want to play baseball.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:44.41,0:01:46.25,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,K-Kamiyama...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:46.66,0:01:49.21,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,Thanks! Courage is springing up\Nin my heart now!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:49.21,0:01:52.38,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,If my words help,\NI'll help you as much as you want.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:52.38,0:01:53.13,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,Yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:53.63,0:01:57.26,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,I don't want to throw cold water on things, \Nbut do you know the rules of baseball?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:57.26,0:01:58.80,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,First, get a buzz cut.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:59.01,0:02:00.05,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,That's not a rule.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:00.05,0:02:03.35,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,First of all, you can't play baseball\Nunless you have nine people.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:03.35,0:02:05.93,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,Don't worry. I'll be all right by myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:05.93,0:02:08.85,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,Like I said, that doesn't work. It's a rule!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:08.85,0:02:11.98,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,I can't quite agree with your opinion, Maeda.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:11.98,0:02:14.28,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,You don't know much about\Nbaseball either, do you?!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:14.28,0:02:17.78,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,Well, I will concede the point to you \Nand admit that you have to have nine people.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:17.78,0:02:20.70,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,But isn't being restricted\N by rules a sad way of living?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:21.49,0:02:23.20,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,It's true that we need rules.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:23.20,0:02:27.79,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,But sometimes breaking them\Ncreates something new.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:27.79,0:02:31.38,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,People who are restricted by rules\Ndon't make any progress in the end.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.38,0:02:33.67,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,That's why you can't make friends, Maeda!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:34.42,0:02:36.55,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,Yeah, what Kamiyama says is right.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.55,0:02:39.84,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,Why don't you stop acting tough and\Nlisten to what your heart's saying?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:39.84,0:02:43.51,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,Before gathering nine people for baseball,\Nshouldn't you find your friends?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:43.51,0:02:47.27,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,Thanks, everyone.\N I don't have any friends and...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.27,0:02:50.60,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,Hey, that's not what we're talking about!\NAnyway, baseball needs nine people!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.60,0:02:54.94,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,If I hold the other team down myself\Nand hit home runs, there won't be a problem.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.94,0:02:55.57,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,Leave it to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.57,0:02:58.93,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,No matter how incredible you pitch\Nto strike out the batters,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.93,0:03:01.78,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,if there's no catcher, it's a wild pitch, \Nso they'll steal first base.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.78,0:03:04.87,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,Don't worry, because I'm the\Nget-'em-out-by-letting-'em-hit type.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.87,0:03:08.00,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,You only know the details about\Nweird stuff, don't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.00,0:03:10.54,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,Anyway, you can't play unless\Nthere's nine players in your team!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.54,0:03:13.75,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,Okay, I got it. All I have to do is gather\Nnine people, right? Don't get so worked up.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.75,0:03:16.71,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,We have many friends,\Nso we'll find enough people soon.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.26,0:03:21.80,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,Sorry, we have only eight people.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.80,0:03:24.51,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,And moreover, two of them aren't human.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.51,0:03:26.85,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,More like, these are the guys we\Nusually hang out with, aren't they?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.85,0:03:28.64,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,Can I ask you something?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.64,0:03:32.60,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,I've counted several times, but\Naren't there only seven people?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.60,0:03:34.48,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,You aren't counting yourself, are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.06,0:03:36.44,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,Five, six, seven... eight...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.40,0:03:40.86,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,I never said that I wanted to play baseball.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.86,0:03:45.37,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,Just accept it, Maeda!\N This is how you start making friends.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.37,0:03:48.20,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,While we were talking,\N we got the ninth member.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.62,0:03:49.95,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,Maeda's old lady.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.95,0:03:51.58,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,Hokuto's lackey would be enough!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.92,0:03:57.34,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,So, we have founded the\NCromartie High School baseball team,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.34,0:04:00.21,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,but first we need to get equipment.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.21,0:04:02.55,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,But we don't have that kind of money.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.22,0:04:05.34,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,So why don't we do\N something about it with our brains?!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.26,0:04:09.68,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,Let's use wooden swords!\NThey can substitute for bats.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.89,0:04:11.43,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,I see. I didn't think of that.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.43,0:04:12.73,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,What about a chest protector?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.73,0:04:15.23,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,It'd be enough if we wrap bleached cotton cloth around our waists.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.23,0:04:18.69,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,If we think about it this way, I guess there are many substitutes for baseball equipment.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.69,0:04:20.53,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,We can do it! We can play baseball!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.57,0:04:23.53,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,{\an7\c&H36503B&\3c&HB6D9CA&\bord3\be2}Stricter Enforcement\N for Motorcycle Gang Month in Effect\NMetropolitan\NPolice Department
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.91,0:04:26.20,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,They won't believe that we're\Ngonna play baseball like this.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.20,0:04:27.70,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,Oh? Where's Hayashida?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.62,0:04:30.12,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,Dear Mother,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.58,0:04:32.41,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,this is the thick woods of Fuji.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.41,0:04:35.58,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,I heard that once you set foot in here,\Nyou can't get out.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.58,0:04:37.75,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,How terrible.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.75,0:04:42.26,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,We only came to Mt. Fuji two days ago\Nfor baseball training camp.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.26,0:04:45.51,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,It was a mistake that we didn't\Nfind some lodging first.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.51,0:04:49.93,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,We got lost in the woods, since some\Nidiot said camping would be cheaper.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.93,0:04:52.14,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,Fine then. It would make you happy\Nif I apologize by dying, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.39,0:04:54.56,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,Hey, Maeda, aren't you going too far?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.56,0:04:58.23,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,It doesn't matter, because he's\Nalways all talk and no action.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.23,0:05:00.36,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,What did you say, moron?!\NAre you making fun of me?!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.36,0:05:01.15,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,Shut up!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.15,0:05:04.86,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,Stop it, both of you! You're only\Nwasting your energy by fighting!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.16,0:05:09.95,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,Sorry. This isn't the time for that, is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.95,0:05:13.75,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,We're all irritated because we're hungry.\NWe should eat something.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.75,0:05:15.79,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,There should still be a can of mackerel.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.79,0:05:17.38,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,And do we have a can opener?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.38,0:05:19.09,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,Don't worry, I have one here.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.09,0:05:20.63,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,Generally in this kind of situation,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.63,0:05:24.38,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,it often ends up that there's canned food,\Nbut no can opener.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.38,0:05:25.93,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,Well done, Maeda.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.93,0:05:27.59,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,If I do say so myself,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.59,0:05:30.68,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,I never lose my cool under any circumstances.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.68,0:05:33.39,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,It's all over if you panic in this kind of situation.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.39,0:05:36.31,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,Everyone needs to settle down and act calmly.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.31,0:05:38.40,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,But that's not the canned mackerel.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.40,0:05:39.23,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,Mecha-ratta!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.23,0:05:40.69,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,The canned mackerel is this one!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.23,0:05:45.28,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,The sun went down and it's getting\Ncolder and quieter around here.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.20,0:05:49.45,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,Are we gonna die here like this?!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.45,0:05:53.08,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,I still had a lot of things that I wanted to do!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.08,0:05:53.95,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,For example?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.16,0:05:57.04,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,For example... well...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.04,0:05:59.04,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,No, you don't have to force yourself to find it.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.29,0:06:03.63,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,We're just sixteen years old.\NIs this how it's gonna end for us?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.88,0:06:05.88,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,What the hell should we do?
